title: 12 x Strawberry Buddy Bare Root Plants - Grow Your Own Strawberries - Bare Root Strawberry Runners - Fruit Plant (Regular Packaging)
features: Strawberry 'Buddy' was been bred for both disease resistance and fruit quality; the strawberries are firm and resist bruising when they are packaged and transported.
These Strawberry plants are everbearing - they fruit from mid July almost until the first frosts.
Strawberry ‘Buddy’ is an easy to grow and reasonably hardy bare root runner, and can be planted or potted in planters, pots, containers, or baskets.
This listing includes 12 Bare Root Strawberry Runners.
Add the option of plastic-free packaging and help the environment, and we will cover 60% of the additional cost.
description: Product Description Are fruit plants easy to grow and maintain? Yes, most are beginner-friendly. They need sun, water, and occasional feeding. Berries are especially easy and low-maintenance. How are fruit plants delivered? Plants are sent potted or bare-root, depending on season. All are securely packed and have planting instructions in the listing. When will my plant produce fruit? Most fruit plants crop in summer to autumn. Exact timing depends on variety – check listings for harvest seasons. Do fruit plants need full sun? Most do best in full sun (6+ hrs/day), though some like currants and gooseberries can tolerate partial shade. Are fruit plants suitable for growing in the UK climate? Yes, many fruit plants are hardy and bred to thrive in UK weather, including apples, berries, plums, figs and more.
